### Aranasi
Hideous eight-legged demons called the Aranasi have been sighted among the ranks of the Burning Legion, acting variously as fodder, soldiers and commanders.
Their life cycle is rapid, hatched from eggs as spider-like creatures before rapidly growing into intelligent arachnoid monsters. They have a mastery over their natural venom, which can be frighteningly deadly, and as they invade territories they are seen transforming whole regions into breeding pits of festering pools and skittering death.

***Spider Queens.*** As female aranasi mature, they undergo a transformation. Becoming significantly more intelligent, they stand up on two of their many legs, with the others splayed behind them like wings, and typically take the role of commanders among the Legion, gaining lofty royal titles and choosing consorts.

***The Silk Road.*** Aranasi broodmothers command dangerous and tricky magic, moulding captured territories into their own silken palaces via their race's webbing. Stepping into such a parlour can be extraordinarily dangerous, as any and all nearby aranasi, from the old to the newly-hatched, will come to the aid of their queen.

___
