### Infernal
*"We never paid any heed to the ancient prophecies. Like fools we clung to the old hatreds, and fought as we had for generations. Until the day the sky rained fire... and a new enemy came among us. We stand now, upon the brink of destruction... for the Reign of Chaos has come at last."*

A cloudy sky, casting shadow over a battlefield. An army of demons swarms, held back bravely by the world's defenders. Suddenly, an assault that no warrior can hold back - breaching through the cloud cover far above, streaking from the sky with a burning, flaming trail of sick green fire, falls a meteor. It slams into the earth, shattering bones and burning skin and armour away with its impact. The defending soldiers, wounded but not yet broken, watch in horror as the burning boulder cracks, moves, and unfolds. Crags become shoulders, arms and legs. Flames give it a vaguely humanoid shape, capped by hideous green eyes in a skull-like face. An infernal has landed among them, a construct of pure destruction, and its sole purpose is to break them.

***Infernal Constructs.*** Ever-burning, the Legion's infernals are crafted on their own worlds out of flaming cores and black rock. They are thoughtless, having no desires or needs, and follow only one instruction - destroy. They are among the Legion's most deadly and feared weapons, and their summoning invariably precedes doom and terror.

***Blazing Invasion.*** Infernals are sometimes deployed en masse by summoners, and predictably, the arrival of hundreds of blazing meteors alone can cause untold damage. As they awaken, the infernals will often do the job of breaking a siege, tearing defenses open and burning away any opposition.

***Immolation and Destruction.*** Little can harm their rocky form, and their Fel cores break magic cast upon them. Their constantly burning bodies set alight anyone foolish enough to go close, and their sheer strength will smash any survivors.
 

___
