### Dread Lord
*“I'm always on the winning side.” - Varimathras*

The dreaded infiltrators of the demon army, and arguably the most valuable and respected species among the Burning Legion, the Nathrezim race are perhaps second only to the Eredar themselves in the eyes of their dark master. It is hard to overstate the impact that the Dreadlords have had on the entire Great Dark, as their insidious efforts have led them to have a hand in almost every major event since before the Burning Legion was even created.
Pale skin, dark eyes, and vicious fangs mark the faces of evil. They are vampiric demons with a natural skill for manipulation, cruelty and espionage, far more likely to use their powers to turn others to evil than to do something as crass and direct as combat - though their prowess in combat is legendary. Acting as high commanders and infiltrators for the Legion, many are seen ordering grand armies into new and confusing positions using information about their foes that they themselves have gathered. Their ability to change their shape and addle or even control the minds of mortals has led to intense distrust and confusion among their enemies, which suits the dreadlords perfectly.

***Vampiric Desires.*** The nathrezim are well known for their thirst for blood, hungering constantly for the vital fluid. this hunger fuels them in combat, and they will drain the lives of their victims until there is nothing left. Even their minions, children of the night such as insects or bats, will thirst for blood, never to be satisfied.

***Master Infiltrators.*** It is said that, at any time, in any place, someone you know may be a dreadlord in disguise. Their sheer skill for gathering information, manipulation and espionage is their greatest strength, and has led the Legion to countless victories. There are no lines they will not cross to further their master's goals, stealing knowledge and power from every world and every realm, even the land of the dead. Some dreadlord spies have gone years, or decades, unmasked.

***Makers of Villains.*** Ironically, their greatest impact on history may be their ability to influence the creation of even greater threats, and not always on purpose. They have had a hand in the creation of some of Azeroth's greatest threats, making ripples and waves far beyond the scope of comprehension. In hushed tones, it is said that they even had a hand in the corruption of the Dark Titan Sargeras - though none would dare claim this as fact.
 
 


\pagebreak
___
___
> ## Dread Lord
> *Large fiend (demon), chaotic evil*
> ___
> - **Armor Class** 17 (natural armor)
> - **Hit Points** 209 (22d10 + 88)
> - **Speed** 30 ft., fly 30 ft.
> ___
> |  STR  |  DEX  |  CON  |  INT  |  WIS  |  CHA  |
> |:-----:|:-----:|:-----:|:-----:|:-----:|:-----:|
> |19 (+4)|18 (+4)|19 (+4)|21 (+5)|16 (+3)|21 (+5)|
> ___
> - **Saving Throws** Dex +10, Wis +9, Cha +11
> - **Skills** Perception +9, Persuasion +11, Deception +17
> - **Damage Resistances** psychic; bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing from nonmagical attacks
> - **Senses** darkvision 60 ft., passive Perception 19
> - **Languages** Eredun; the dread lord can understand any physical language and communicate with any creature that speaks one
> - **Challenge** 17 (18,000 XP)
> ___
> ***Demonic Terror.*** Any non-demonic creature who sees the dread lord must make a DC 19 Wisdom saving throw. On a failure, the creature is frightened of the dread lord, and must repeat the saving throw at the start of each turn. A creature who succeeds on the saving throw is immune to this effect for 24 hours.
>
>***Legendary Resistance (3/Day).*** If the dread lord fails a saving throw, it can choose to succeed instead.
>
> ***Spellcasting.*** The dread lord is a 12th-level spellcaster. The dread lord's spellcasting ability is Charisma (spell save DC 19, +11 to hit with spell attacks). The dread lord has the following spells prepared:
>
> Cantrip (at will): *friends*, *prestidigitation*, *fire bolt*, 
> <br>    *minor illusion*
> <br>1st level (4 slots): *sleep*, *false life*, *cause fear*, 
<br>     *charm person*, *hex*
> <br>2nd level (3 slots): *detect thoughts*, *invisibility*, *hold*
> <br>    *person*, *ray of enfeeblement*
> <br>3rd level (3 slots): *gaseous form*, *vampiric touch*, 
> <br>    *bestow curse*, *hypnotic pattern*
> <br>4th level (3 slots): *blight*, *hallucinatory terrain*
> <br>5th level (2 slots): *hold monster*, *scrying*
> <br>6th level (1 slots): *mass suggestion*
>
> ***Vampiric Aura.*** Whenever the dread lord or allies within 30 feet of it deal necrotic damage, they regain hit points equal to half the necrotic damage dealt. 
> 
>### Actions
> ***Multiattack.*** The dread lord makes two vampiric claw attacks.
>
> ***Vampiric Claw.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* +10 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. *Hit:* 13 (2d8 + 4) slashing damage plus 18 (4d8) necrotic damage. 
>
> ***Charm.*** The dread lord targets one humanoid it can see within 30 feet of itself. If the target can see the dread lord, the target must succeed on a DC 19 Wisdom saving throw or be charmed. The charmed target regards the nathrezim as a trusted friend to be heeded and protected. The target isn't under the dread lord's control, but it takes the dread lord's requests and action in the most favorable way.
> <br>    Each time the dread lord or its companions do anything harmful to the target, it can repeat the saving throw, ending the effect on itself on a success. Otherwise, the effect last 24 hours or until the dread lord is destroyed, is on a different place of existence than the target, or takes a bonus action to end this effect.
>
> ***Carrion Swarm (Recharge 5-6).*** The dread lord summons a swarm of biting insects around himself. All creatures in a 30 foot line starting from the dread lord must make a DC 18 Dexterity saving throw or take 14 (4d6) piercing damage and 14 necrotic damage , or half as much on a successful save. A creature who fails this saving throw also can only take either their action or bonus action on their turn, not both for 1 minute, or until they succeed on a DC 19 Constitution saving throw, which can be made at the end of each of their turns. 
> ### Legendary Actions
> The dread lord can take 3 legendary actions, choosing from the options below. Only one legendary action option can be used at a time and only at the end of another creature's turn. The dread lord regains spent legendary actions at the start of its turn.
>
> **Move.** The dread lord can move up to its speed without 
> <br>    provoking opportunity attacks
> <br>**Attack.** The dread lord makes one vampiric claw attack.
> <br>**Sleep (Costs 2 Actions).** The nathrezim cast *sleep* using 
> <br>    one of its spell slots.

