### Pit Lord
*"Yes... yes! I can feel his burning eyes upon me, he is close...so close. And then your world will be unmade, your lives as nothing!" - Mannoroth the Destructor*

The annihilan are perhaps the most fearsome, dangerous and destructive of all of the demonic races. Known as Pit Lords, these colossal creatures act as high commanders of the Legion's invasion forces, and are rarely content to command anywhere other than in the field of battle.
Built like mountains, their reptilian tails and four cawed legs give rise to immensely powerful upper bodies, protected by armour as thick as doors. Their barrel-like arms typically wield swords or polearms the length of buildings, capable of shattering the ground beneath them. Their gigantic wings are worthless for flight, as they are simply too heavy, but are like a shield of steel, while their backs, from head to tail, are lit by a blazing mane of emerald flames. Their faces, tusked and filled with nests of tiny razor-sharp teeth, spew flame with every breath.
Pit lords use little magic or cunning, preferring instead to end battles decisively using their brute strength and fearsome tactics to overcome an enemy. Their command over their inferiors is unquestioned, and failure is punished by death. They respect nothing but strength, and seek nothing but total destruction.

***Unrelenting Power.*** Pit lords do not give up. Ever. Unless it is completely killed, nothing will stop its slaughter. There have been pit lords with their hands removed, who have simply replaced them with weapons. Pit lords imprisoned will literally never stop raging and heaving at their bonds. Refusal to obey them will result in extreme rage, while those given orders will put the entire being into reaching their goal, no cost too small.

***Legacy of Death.*** Even death does not stop a pit lord's malice. Their bodies are loaded with overwhelming power, and upon their death all of it is unleashed at once in a catastrophic explosion. Even afterwards, their blood has a hideous corruptive potency that will never go away; drinking the blood of a pit lord is enough to permanently transform a creature unregognisably, while the blood is also able to deeply corrupt the land around it until it too is unrecognisable. This blood has been seen raising the dead, and even congealing into living globules. The death of a pit lord is n ongoing catastrophe that may take decades to be cleared.

***Bloody Enslavement.*** The blood of a pit lord's most famous property is also its worst; when consumed, a creature will be bound to the demon. Enslaved, unable to resist its will, and overwhelmed with bloodlust, creatures so enslaved will be under command until the moment of the demon's death. This was first seen when the demon Mannoroth's blood was consumed by the orcish race, turning their brown skin green.
 


\pagebreak
___
___
